casebody.data:
[561 U.S. 476] BRUCE WEYHRAUCH, Petitioner v UNITED STATES 561 U.S. 476, 130 S. Ct. 2971,

177 L. Ed. 2d 705,

2010 U.S. LEXIS 5254 [No. 08-1196] Argued December 8, 2009. Decided June 24, 2010. APPEARANCES OF COUNSEL ARGUING CASE Donald B. Ayer argued the cause for petitioner. Michael R. Dreeben argued the cause for respondent.

[561 U.S. 476]

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is vacated, and the case is remanded to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit for further consideration in light of Skilling v. United States, ante, p. 358, 130 S. Ct. 2896, 177 L. Ed. 2d 619.
